reality by accepting large expenditures for national defense, environmental
regulation, or publicly funded education. He does not believe in national parks
("private <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">stewards</ENAMEX>" will exercise "proper stewardship"). Nor does he believe in
military <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">conscription</ENAMEX> in wartime ("[t]he libertarian believes that <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">people</ENAMEX> will
voluntarily defend a <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">country</ENAMEX> worth defending").

            Though
this version of libertarianism seems to flirt with anarchism, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Boaz</ENAMEX> isn't
